<i>Posted by Wylias on 10-23-2001 04:46 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon12.gif" alt="Wink" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p>[Edit to answer Parson's question] To reply to the last /send you recieved, just hit 'r' without bringing up a typing line.<br />
<br />
The friends list mini-window is your friend. Keep it up all the time, it updates in real time. Set the transparency to match your personal preference.<br />
<br />
When adding friends to your list, they not only have to be online, but in the same zone. All of the outdoors (and the small towns) are considered one zone, but dungeons and the capital are their own separate zones.<br />
<br />
Keep your bow and both hands (whether weapons or shield) hotkeyed on the same hotkey bank to allow for fast swapping of weapon types. If you're an archer, keep your critical shot hotkey on this bank as well.<br />
<br />
It's better to hunt in areas that have few players, since you get a bonus for killing enemies that have been up for a while.<br />
<br />
If you can do so safely, bring your group to the enemy, not the enemy to the group. You get an experience bonus for killing stuff near where they spawned.<br />
<br />
Sometimes it's better to fight a 2 or 3 oranges or reds than one purple at a time, you get a bonus for killing the friends your enemy calls for help. This calling for help is often known as BAF (bring a friend).<br />
<br />
Large groups can take on reds or purples typically, this is incredible experience. After a while of super-grouping, take some time soloing greens or working on tradeskill consignments to make up for the lower cash profits grouping provides.<font face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
Wylias, Celtic Ranger; Galahad<br />
<br />
The annoying lucradan says, "You can't hurt me!"<br />
You prepare your shot (7.5s to fire, target is in range)<br />
The annoying lucradan says, "Ha, ha, ha! You can't catch me!"<br />
You shoot the annoying lucradan with your bow and hit for 122 damage!<br />
The annoying lucradan says, "No!!! But I am invincible! I'll be back, you wait and see!"<br />
You say, "Sure you will. In the meantime, I'll kill all your little friends, too."</font></p>
