<i>Posted by Swiftbow on 10-23-2001 04:55 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Nightfox, just hit r<br />
<br />
some other hints i have learned.<br />
<br />
For Kill tasks, check the named guards found closest to areas with mobs your area. For example, level 10 might check around Dvalin, or level 14 might check the tower with the banker at the myrkwood border.<br />
<br />
Why? Because if you are getting kill tasks in a regiion far below your level, say the level 15 recieving tasks in Mulurn, then you will have to run a great distance each time to the mobs and back.<br />
<br />
You can take your text down to an Alpha of 0, which will make the text white and the boc completely clear. A great way to have it, unless you are in a snow region.<br />
<br />
USe the ~ key to look around your character. great when being chased. All you do is hit autorun in a safe directin, and then use this technique to move the camera and look behind you. You can then see if you are still being chased.<br />
<br />
It is also great to use when on horseback or when you /follow someone. Enjoy the scenery.<br />
<br />
After the kill taks mob dies, hit /task to determine if your mission is complete (will say "Return to so and so for your reward".)<br />
If another player or pet got the last hit, your task is NOT complete. Quite a bummer to run all the way back to discover this.<font face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
