<i>Posted by Lantharius on 11-05-2001 08:40 PM:</i>

<p><b> Bow Range</b></p>

<p>I stole this from another ranger, but it works nicely for determining if you are in range to fire an arrow...<br />
<br />
Manually determine if you are in range of a monster.  Move back and forth until you are in the maximum range.  Then use mouse-look and make sure you are looking over your shoulders (so you can see the ground and the monster in front of you).  Next, press F5 (auto target I think).  There is now a cursor target at your feet.  Move the cursor target out to the monster at the edge of your range.<br />
<br />
Now when you find another monster, just turn on this auto-target cursor, to quickly find if it is in your range.  This will save you time, so you don't have to wait for that "target out of range" message.  You can easily "eyeball" it this way.  This is critical when in RvR combat, as wasted time targeting can mean death.<font face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
Lantharius Trollbane<br />
29 Lurikeen Ranger<br />
Percival</font></p>
