<i>Posted by Bankok on 11-07-2001 03:29 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>- When in RvR, turn your torch off.<br />
<br />
-  If your group is in trouble, do everything possible to make sure one rezzer makes it out alive, much easier, and much cheaper than all having to do tombstone runs.<br />
<br />
-  If in Hibernia, do not kill Lucradains for your first 17 levels, them bastages love to aggro once they are hostile.<br />
<br />
-  If its a static spawn, the BAF code is definately in play, roaming mobs for the most part can be pulled singly.<br />
<br />
-  Take up a tradeskill, it breaks up the monotony and you can make some nice cash after 350 or so.  (Sorry to ruin your secret Yosh.)  Best bet is to just make items until 250 or so, and then start doing consignment.<br />
<br />
-  If you are doing a tradeskill make friends with other tradeskill people.  I.E.  I can make about 1-2 gold per consignment now because I have a tailor make the parts I need for Scale Armor.<br />
<br />
-  Sometimes the easiest way to raise a secondary skill like metalcrafting is to start another tradeskill.  I.E.  When I needed to raise metalworking to do scale armor, I did weaponcrafting to get the skill raises.<br />
<br />
- Neat little trick in Dungeons when most of your party is wiped out a ways inside the dungeon, and the rezzers zoned.  Have everyone disband, and then have a stealth class start the group.  They can then go down and invite those who are dead, and you can then rez them from a distance without having to fight back to them.</p>
