Absolutely.  I do digress a bit on the metalworking skill.  I tried the weapon smith route and it was painful (not expensive though).  Then I found that the best way to raise metalworking is to make sellable trinkets (hinges and brackets).  Do not be afraid of the material cost.  THE PRODUCT SELL BACK AT LESS THAN 10% LOST.  I raised my metalworking to 400 with the cost of 3~4 golds.  And it is fast.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><br />
- Neat little trick in Dungeons when most of your party is wiped out a ways inside the dungeon, and the rezzers zoned.  Have everyone disband, and then have a stealth class start the group.  They can then go down and invite those who are dead, and you can then rez them from a distance without having to fight back to them. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
